@node intro "Introduction"

NSA Security was originally written by me for a mate's BBS to keep his 
private sections VERY private :)

The spec was simple, if a user isn't on the list then they shouldn't even
get to a password screen on anything that could give the game away!

As a result, NSA Secure was born nearly 1 year ago :)  It has simple to
use configs & a selection of ways to put a nosey user off finding out
what it's protecting :)

@endnode
@node sysreq "System Requirements"

You need to be running MAX's BBS (any version should do!) and have something
you want to hide! (Usually seems to be porn or warez nowadays :/ )

You must have the NSAkeyfile.key file in your S: directory for this door 
to run (Like most NSA doors)...

You can obtain 1 FREE(!!!) by calling Redrum BBS, or by emailing your 
details to nsa_design@hotmail.com :)
(See the door for more info!)

@endnode
@node inst "Installation & Configs"

The easy bit :^)... Just use the following:-

	Lha X NSA_Secure.Lha Doors:
	
This will work for any system that has Doors: assigned to where the BBS has
it's doors..

You will need the NSAkeyfile.key in S: for this program to work.
This is FREE!!!!!!!!..  Run the door for more info :)

A director called SEC will be created in Doors: for the program.

The reason why the door & dir are called SEC is to allow longer path names
for the config files :)

Running
~~~~~~~

Execution under MAX's BBS 1.54 or /X\ Pro v1 - v1.70
In the menu editor set.

Key:   Function:  Extra:    Lo Acc:    Hi Acc:	  Filename/Name/Dest/Path:
 '       34	    0 	      100	10000	  Doors:Sec/Sec ConfigFile

ConfigFile is the full path and name of your config file!
e.g.  
Doors:Sec/Sec S:MyWarez.config
Doors:Sec/Sec Work:Private.text

You may have as many config files for as many parts of the BBS that you
require :)))))


Config File
~~~~~~~~~~~

The config file can be located ANYWHERE on you HD!!!

It's in the following format:-

Line 1	- The menu number to jump to on a successful entry :)
Line 2	- The ANSI file to display for the password entry display.
Line 3	- Action to be taken if user is not on access list.  See below.
Lines 4+  User/Password list!
	  Just have the first line for user name & second for password for
	  as many users as you want to give access to :)))))
	  
	  Names & Passwords are not case-sensitive :)


Look at the configs supplied for help :)


Actions (Line 3)
~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~

If a user isn't on your access list then you probably don't even want them 
to know anything about it :))))

Therefore, NSA Security supports 3 differant ways to throwing a user off
the trail! :)


Method 1 - The fake error message <G>
	   Simply have line 3 contain a fake error message for an imaginary
	   door program!
	   e.g.
	   Error! Sysop Upload Door FAILED!  Return code (68).
	   
Method 2 - Menu Jumping! :)))))
	   Simply have the first char of the line as a : and then have a
	   menu to jump to if the user doesn't have access!
	   It's usually best to make a user jump to a normal logout menu 
	   or the furthest part of the BBS & if they ask, just say it's a 
	   menu jumper :) heheheheh <EG>
	   e.g.
	   :23
	   
Number 3 - The Larch..  ..  Seriously...

Method 3 - The ANSI display! :)))
	   If you have the first char to be a < then NSA Security will just
	   display an ansi file, then quit.
	   You could have this ansi as a statistics file with normal 
	   auto-inserts so peeps wouldn't think anything about it :)
	   e.g.
	   <BBS:Text/Statistics.text

The password prompt appears at ANSI co-ordinate 31,13.  This can not be
changed in the current release!


You can also have NSA Secure running in the maindoor.text file :)
This gives you the ability for having 1 main menu for elite users & 1 for
normal users! :))))


NEW IN v1.10!
~~~~~~~~~~~~~

NSA Security now hides the password from display.  This was requested by
a user... :)

Any chars are now displayed as *'s.

@endnode

@node inuse "Using NSA Security when started :))))))"

When the door is started, it loads up one of the configs specified and
scans it to see if the user is on it.

If they are then they get 3 chances to enter the correct password to gain
access to your private menu.

ALL actions are logged to a file called Security.log in Doors:Sec/

If the user isn't on the list they they will be delt with according to
line 3 of the config file :)))))


It's up to you what you use this door for, either for members file sections,
sysop menu, porn, warez etc etc...  I don't really care!

All I can say is if you have illegal files, you still stand the chance of
being busted & having all of your gear confiscated!


I think that's about it now :)))))))))))))

(Read the credz & greetz :))) )


@endnode

